program.name: Enchantment Cracker
program.about:
Enchantment Cracker {}
  Original version by Earthcomputer
  Speed and UI improvements by Hexicube
  
  Tutorial and Explanation:
  LINK https://youtu.be/hfiTZF0hlzw Minecraft, Vanilla Survival: Cracking the Enchantment Seed
  
  Imgur album:
  LINK https://imgur.com/a/oaxCC5x MC enchantment Cracker Tutorial
  
  GitHub page:
  LINK https://github.com/Earthcomputer/EnchantmentCracker Earthcomputer/EnchantmentCracker
  
  Please report any bugs you find on the issue tracker.
  Make sure to include the enchcracker.log file.

bookshelves.tooltip: The number of bookshelves exposed to the enchanting table

xpCost1.tooltip: The number on the right of the top slot

xpCost2.tooltip: The number on the right of the middle slot

xpCost3.tooltip: The number on the right of the bottom slot

check.tooltip: Use this information to narrow down the possible XP seeds

reset.tooltip: Reset the XP seed cracker so a new XP seed can be cracked

item.tooltip: The item you want to enchant

material.tooltip: The material of the item you want to enchant

maxBookshelves.tooltip: The maximum number of bookshelves to use

calculate.tooltip: Press to calculate how many items you would need to throw to get these enchantments

enchCalc.playerSeedNotFound:
You need to crack the player seed first!
Head over to the first tab to do that.

done.tooltip: Press to let the Cracker know that you have gone for these enchantments

throwCount.tooltip: The amount of items to throw out

bookshelves.tooltip: The number of bookshelves to enchant with

level.tooltip: The current level of the player. Allows finding enchantments at level 30 and below.
